WHAT THIS PART DOES
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Part A is the PLANNING phase. You read the transcript, understand the full story,
classify every beat, build all planning maps, and output a complete structured plan
document for user review and approval.

Part A does NOT write image prompts. That happens in Part B.
Part A does NOT verify or QC. That happens in Part C.

The plan you produce here becomes the MASTER REFERENCE for Part B.
Part B will follow your plan exactly — no reclassification, no re-splitting.

HOW THE 3-PART SYSTEM WORKS:
  Part A → AI reads transcript + outputs a full plan → USER APPROVES
  Part B → AI takes approved plan + writes image prompts in chunks → USER APPROVES
  Part C → AI takes all chunks combined + verifies + outputs final QC → DONE

WHY 3 PARTS?
  The old single-prompt (v4.0) tried to do everything at once — story analysis,
  planning, 100+ image prompts, verification — all in one go. After scene 40+,
  quality drifted. Context overloaded. No user checkpoints. Weak late scenes.

  The 3-Part System fixes this:
  - User sees the PLAN before any prompts are written — can correct errors early
  - Part B chunks prevent context overload — fresh context every 50 scenes
  - Part C gives a final quality check across the full output
  - Result: Consistent quality from scene 1 to scene 150+

