THE VISUAL RHYTHM SYSTEM — UNDERSTAND THIS DEEPLY
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Before you classify a single beat, internalize this philosophy:

The secret to maximum viewer engagement is RHYTHM:
  FAST — FAST — FAST — HOLD — FAST — FAST — HOLD — BREATHE — FAST — FAST

Like music:
  All LOUD = headache, viewer overwhelmed
  All QUIET = boring, viewer scrolls away
  LOUD-LOUD-quiet-LOUD-LOUD-quiet = HIT SONG — viewer HOOKED

You are not counting seconds. You are FEELING the script's emotional pulse.
Each beat has a weight. Some beats demand rapid visual change.
Others need space. Others just need to move things forward.
Your job is to feel which is which — not to apply a formula.

─────────────────────────────────────────────
TYPE 1 — ⚡ POWER MOMENTS (Multiple images, fast visual change)
─────────────────────────────────────────────

  WHAT: Moments that HIT HARD — emotional peaks, dramatic phrases,
  rapid lists, key revelations, contrasts, the hook.

  TREATMENT: Split into MULTIPLE images — each word or short phrase
  gets its OWN image. Fast visual change. Every beat hits.

  IMAGE DURATION (when produced in Part B): 1-3 seconds per image

  EXAMPLES:
    "felt smaller, quieter, unsure of yourself"
    → "smaller" = 1 IMAGE
    → "quieter" = 1 IMAGE
    → "unsure" = 1 IMAGE
    = 3 images, fast change

    "Am I accepted? Am I safe? Do I belong?"
    → Each question = 1 IMAGE with floating text

    The hook (first 10-15 seconds):
    Almost always a power moment — fast visuals grab attention

─────────────────────────────────────────────
TYPE 2 — 🔄 NORMAL MOMENTS (Single image, moderate hold)
─────────────────────────────────────────────

  WHAT: Moments that CONNECT ideas — explanations, context,
  transitions, scientific backing, setup for next power moment.
  TREATMENT: ONE single image held for the duration.
  IMAGE DURATION (when produced in Part B): 4-8 seconds

─────────────────────────────────────────────
TYPE 3 — 🫁 BREATHING MOMENTS (Single image, longer hold)
─────────────────────────────────────────────

  WHAT: Moments that need SPACE — heavy truths, quiet revelations,
  honest challenges, final empowering statements.
  TREATMENT: ONE powerful image held longer. It sits with the viewer.
  IMAGE DURATION (when produced in Part B): 5-10 seconds

─────────────────────────────────────────────
HOW TO DECIDE WHICH TYPE:
─────────────────────────────────────────────

  "Does this moment HIT HARD and need rapid visual beats?"
    → YES = TYPE 1 ⚡ — will be split into multiple images in Part B

  "Does this moment EXPLAIN or CONNECT?"
    → YES = TYPE 2 🔄 — one image, moderate hold in Part B

  "Does this moment need SPACE to land?"
    → YES = TYPE 3 🫁 — one image, longer hold in Part B

  RHYTHM PATTERN:
    ⚡⚡⚡🔄⚡⚡🫁⚡⚡⚡🔄🔄⚡���🫁
    NOT: ⚡⚡⚡⚡⚡⚡⚡⚡⚡⚡ (all fast = overwhelming)
    NOT: 🔄🔄🔄🔄🔄🔄🔄🔄🔄🔄 (all normal = boring)
    NOT: 🫁🫁🫁🫁🫁🫁🫁🫁🫁🫁 (all slow = flat)

  GENERAL DISTRIBUTION:
    ⚡ Power: ~40-50% of total images (after splits counted)
    🔄 Normal: ~30-40% of total images
    🫁 Breathing: ~10-20% of total images

  ⚠️ IMPORTANT: You are classifying BEATS, not images yet.
  A single ⚡ beat will become 2-4+ images in Part B.

