STEP 5: RUN SCENE COUNT CALCULATOR
═══════════════════════════════════════════

  PURPOSE: Calculate the expected total number of scenes.

  FORMULA:
  ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
  Power Moment beats    × avg splits per beat  = Power images
  Normal Moment beats   × 1 image per beat     = Normal images
  Breathing Moment beats × 1 image per beat    = Breathing images
                                      TOTAL =  Expected scene count
  ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

  EXAMPLE:
    Power:    ~30 beats × avg 3 splits = ~90 images
    Normal:   ~26 beats × 1            = ~26 images
    Breathing:~18 beats × 1            = ~18 images
    EXPECTED TOTAL: ~134 scenes

  WARNING CHECKS:
  □ Is the expected total realistic for this transcript length?
  □ Is any section over-split (more images than script beats justify)?
  □ Are breathing moments enough (at least 10% of total)?
  □ Does the count make sense given the rhythm classification?

